cutthecrap.utils.striterators

Class Striterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • cutthecrap.utils.striterators.Striterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICloseable, ICloseableIterator, IStriterator, IStriterator.ITailOp, Enumeration, Iterator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    XPropertyIterator

    public class Striterator
extends Object
implements IStriterator, IStriterator.ITailOp, ICloseableIterator
    Striterator - transformation and mapping patterns over java Iterator s.

    Allows wrapping of an iterator so that extensions may add type specific next methods.

    The IFilter objects passed to addFilter allow selection criteria for the iterated objects. The addTypeFilter method allows easy specification of a class type restriction.

      • availableTailOp

        public Iterator availableTailOp()
        If this Striterator has not been overriden then return the source iterator, or even better, try and recurse to the nested tailOp if available. This has been disabled since it appears to have a negative effect. To reactivate, uncomment the ITailOp implementation declaration. TODO: Investigate apparent performance degradation with activation
